{
  "stem": "15174.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, there was sort of a courtyard.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "The synagogue was in the back of the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "The school was on one side.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And in front of this courtyard, separating the courtyard from the street, was the school gym.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Well, when my mother took me back to school after Kristallnacht, we came to the school and I saw all the windows of the gym were broken.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Apparently that's how they had gotten into the courtyard to get to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And then when we walked into the courtyard, I could see that the synagogue had been burned down.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "I could not only see it, but I could smell it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "You could still smell the smoldering smoke.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I can-- it sounds funny, but I can still sort of smell that smell.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "It's something that you just can't forget.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And of course, it-- I don't know if you can imagine even what it felt like to know that the synagogue that you had been attending with your parents-- I told you I used to go with my father on Saturday mornings-- was burned down.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "It was burned down because people didn't like Jews, namely me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "I mean, it was-- it was just a terrible, terrible [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] feeling.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "You really felt violated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But, you know, one-- one-- in spite of all these things happening, one tries to carry on as normally as one can.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "I continued to go to school until January of 1939, when I got diphtheria.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "So it wasn't enough that my mother-- my father was in Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
